*	Governments around the world are publishing their requirements to
allow office workers to return to their offices
*	Desks 2metres apart, no canteens, maximum 2 in a lift.... with these
measures to stay in place until a vaccine is available - mid 2021?
*	All possible, but your average office building will now only support
20% to 30% of the staff it supported before the crisis
*	Many companies are finding that whilst their employees can work from
home on existing projects, the exchange of ideas, generation of new
initiatives and sense of purpose is significantly impacted by remote working
*	So if each employee can only visit the office 1 or 2 days a week,
how to organise who attends the office on which day?
*	This practical problem is likely to accelerate the biggest change to
white collar working practices since the invention of the desktop computer
*	Companies will look to bring project teams into the office at the
same time, not organisational units - to make most use of the face to face
time
*	So companies will start to adopt a more fluid style of organisation,
out with hierarchies and in with transient project teams supplemented by
freelancers where necessary
*	Senior managers will adopt a new management style supported more by
software such as Trello, leaning less on line managers 
*	Senior managers will also talk more directly to employees culturally
- adopting an adult to adult cultural discussion compared to the current
hierarchical adult child cultural discussion
*	Software such as IndigoMetrics will be crucial to support this adult
to adult discourse and to produce the data required to dynamically manage
the culture of an organisation and promote the soft skills that the
organisation requires
*	Of course some tasks are still best organised through hierarchically
organised teams, but these tasks tend to be the ones that are being
automated away in any case


*	So will the practical challenges of social distancing drive a major
shift in the way we organise our companies - and the future of work?

 

 


